3EKindle%3C%2Fa%3E%20ebook%20readers%2C%20devices%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Famazon-echo-buying-guide%5C%22%3EAmazon%20Echo%3C%2Fa%3E%20smart%20speakers%2C%20and%20other%20consumer%20electronics%20also%20offered%20on%20the%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20a%20physical%20Amazon%20Books%20store%20provided%20a%20new%20way%20to%20interact%20with%20customers%20%E2%80%94%20a%20physical%20retail%20space%20for%20browsing%20and%20purchases%20outside%20the%20brand's%20traditional%20online%20storefront%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20also%20a%20new%20vector%20for%20offering%20value%20to%20Amazon's%20lucrative%20Prime%20membership.%20Products%20in%20the%20store%20had%20two%20prices%3A%20one%20for%20ordinary%20customers%2C%20and%20a%20discounted%20price%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-is-amazon-prime%5C%22%3EAmazon%20Prime%3C%2Fa%3E%20subscribers.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAmazon%20Books%20growth%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20Amazon%20Books%20location%20opened%20in%20San%20Diego%2C%20California.%20Subsequent%20stores%20appeared%20in%20cities%20like%20Portland%2C%20Oregon%3B%20Bellevue%2C%20Washington%3B%20Chicago%2C%20Illinois%3B%20Atlanta%2C%20Georgia%3B%20Century%20City%2C%20California%3B%20Paramus%2C%20New%20Jersey%3B%20and%20New%20York%20City.%20In%20total%2C%20Amazon%20opened%20two%20dozen%20stores%20across%2012%20states%20and%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20its%20peak%2C%20California%20was%20home%20to%20the%20most%20Amazon%20Books%20stores%2C%20with%20seven%20in%20total.%20Several%20other%20states%20tied%20with%20two%20stores%20each%2C%20including%20Colorado%2C%20Massachusetts%2C%20New%20York%2C%20Texas%2C%20and%20Washington.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20two%20Amazon%20Books%20stores%20were%20identical%3B%20each%20location%20had%20a%20somewhat%20unique%20layout%20and%20inventory.%20Even%20so%2C%20they%20all%20shared%20some%20common%20characteristics.%20Locations%20ranged%20from%203%2C500%20sq.%20ft.%20to%206%2C000%20sq.%20ft.%20In%20addition%2C%20all%20stores%20relied%20on%20the%20same%20general%20retail%20strategy%2C%20with%20a%20mix%20of%20books%20and%20electronic%20devices%20for%20sale%2C%20along%20with%20a%20carefully%20curated%20selection%20of%20other%20products%20chosen%20from%20the%20Amazon%20website's%20inventory.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20most%20bookstores%2C%20books%20at%20Amazon%20Books%20were%20displayed%20face%20out%20rather%20than%20spine%20out%20to%20make%20them%20more%20engaging%20to%20customers.%20Devices%20like%20Kindle%20readers%2C%20Amazon%20Echo%20speakers%2C%20and%20headphones%20were%20on%20display%20in%20demo%20mode%2C%20and%20customers%20were%20encouraged%20to%20explore%20them%2C%20much%20like%20Apple%20retail%20stores.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20end%20of%20Amazon%20Books%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20March%202%2C%202022%2C%20Amazon%20announced%20that%20it%20was%20closing%20all%20of%20its%20Amazon%20Books%20retail%20locations.%2C%20including%20all%2024%20permanent%20locations%20and%20a%20small%20array%20of%20pop-up%20shops.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20closures%20were%20part%20of%20a%20larger%20belt-tightening%20at%20Amazon%2C%20where%20a%20total%20of%2068%20retail%20stores%20have%20been%20closed%20in%20total.%20Despite%20the%20continued%20success%20of%20the%20Amazon%20website%2C%20sales%20growth%20in%20brick-and-mortar%20locations%20had%20been%20sluggish%2C%20with%20the%20company%20reporting%20disappointing%20sales.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Famzn-stock%5C%22%3EAmazon's%20stock%3C%2Fa%3E%20price%20dramatically%20underperformed%20compared%20to%20other%20tech%20stocks%2C%20and%20this%20appears%20to%20have%20led%20to%20the%20decision%20to%20pivot%20its%20retail%20strategy%2C%20cutting%20costs%20by%20closing%20retail%20locations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20has%20said%20that%20it%20has%20plans%20to%20continue%20op