_webapp%3D1%26sender_device%3Dpc%26web_id%3D7298122189694748206%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edominated%20their%20FYP.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20users%20who%20did%20complain%20did%20not%20provide%20evidence%20of%20said%20ads%20on%20their%20FYP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20if%20something%20isn't%20flagged%20as%20an%20ad%20on%20TikTok%2C%20either%20with%20an%20%26quot%3Beligible%20for%20commission%26quot%3B%20or%20a%20%26quot%3Bsponsored%26quot%3B%20tag%20at%20the%20bottom%20left%20corner%20of%20the%20screen%2C%20users%20can%20still%20be%20inundated%20with%20content%20encouraging%20them%20to%20buy%20something.%20For%20example%2C%20creators%20can%20show%20us%20items%20for%20product%20reviews%20or%20promote%20their%20businesses%20through%20their%20pages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20at%20Insider%2C%20two%20Gen%20Z%20colleagues%20decided%20to%20take%20on%20the%20laborious%20task%20of%20watching%20500%20TikToks%20each%20to%20determine%20how%20much%20advertising%20we%20consume%20on%20the%20platform%20and%20what%20that%20means%20for%20our%20consumer-centric%20culture%20(and%20our%20sanity).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EOur%20methodology%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20experiment%20was%20conducted%20over%20a%20nearly%20three-hour%20timespan%20on%20a%20Saturday%20night.%20It%20involved%20two%20reporters%3A%20Hannah%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20Southern%20California%2C%20and%20Sebastian%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20Northern%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20a%20rigorous%20science%20experiment%2C%20so%20of%20course%2C%20we%20tracked%20our%20results%20on%20a%20Google%20spreadsheet%20that%20we%20put%20together%20in%2020%20minutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20focused%20solely%20on%20TikTok%20videos%20and%20slideshows%20and%20excluded%20TikTok%20stories%20and%20TikTok%20livestreams%20%E2%80%94%20even%20streams%20that%20were%20explicitly%20there%20to%20sell%20products%2C%20like%20QVC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20five%20categories%20of%20content%20that%20we%20tracked%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewere%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3ERegular%20Content%3A%20This%20is%20your%20average%20TikTok%20cooking%20tutorial%20or%20Get%20Ready%20With%20Me.%20No%20one%20is%20explicitly%20showing%20you%20a%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EAffiliate%20Content%3A%20This%20is%20content%20that%20creators%20make%20to%20receive%20a%20commission%20on%20TikTok.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3ESponsored%20Content%3A%20Also%20called%20a%20paid%20partnership%20on%20TikTok.%20A%20company%20pays%20a%20creator%20to%20talk%20about%20their%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3ETraditional%20Ads%3A%20These%20are%20regular%20ads%20that%20businesses%20pay%20TikTok%20to%20display.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3ESelf-promoting%20of%20a%20business%20or%20product%3A%20A%20company%20or%20individual%20using%20their%20platform%20to%20promote%20products%20or%20services%2C%20but%20it%20isn't%20marked%20as%20an%20ad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EProduct%20Reviews%3A%20These%20aren't%20intended%20to%20advertise%2C%20but%20the%20creators%20still%20display%20products%20and%20speak%20positively%20or%20negatively%20about%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20there%20isn't%20much%20data%20on%20the%20TikTok%20algorithm%20(the%20company%20is%20notoriously%20secretive%20about%20how%20it%20works%20exactly)%2C%20precisely%20how%20our%20actions%20influenced%20the%20algorithm%20%E2%80%94%20or%20if%20there%20was%20any%20effect%20in%20real%20time%20%E2%80%94%20was%20a%20complete%20mystery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20we%20did%20know%20some%20general%20factors%20about%20how%20the%20FYP%20decides%20to%20feed%20us%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20certain%20accounts%2C%20liking%20posts%2C%20and%20even%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-tiktok-algorithm-for-you-page-works-watch-time-report-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehovering%20over%20videos%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20pertain%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsupport.tiktok.com%2Fen%2Fusing-tiktok%2Fexploring-videos%2Fhow-tiktok-recommends-content%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etopic%20of%20interest%3C%2Fa%3E%20aid%20the%20algorithm%20in%20deciding%20what%20to%20show%20you%20next%20%E2%80%94%20this%20includes%20videos%20with%20TikTok%20shop%20links%2C%20according%20to%20a%20TikTok%20spokesperson.%20The%20more%20you%20interact%20with%20shoppable%20content%2C%20the%20more%20the%20algorithm%20gives%20you%20said%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20also%20aware%20that%20our%20content%20suggestions%20would%20be%20different%20based%20on%20our%20individual%20interests%2C%20watch%20times%2C%20locations%2C%20and%20interactions%20with%20the%20app.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20all%20this%20in%20mind%2C%20we%20grabbed%20our%20water%20bottles%2C%20silenced%20our%20Slack%20notifications%2C%20and%20leaped%20into%20the%20TikTok%20abyss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHannah's%20observations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20name%20is%20Hannah%2C%20and%20I%20indulge%20in%20many%20different%20subgenres%20on%20TikTok%20%E2%80%94%20travel%20content%2C%20hair%20and%20beauty%20content%2C%20home%20lifestyle%20content%2C%20and%20social%20justice%20content%20%E2%80%94%20but%20broadly%20speaking%2C%20I'm%20on%20the%20Black%20side%20of%20TikTok.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20my%20FYP%20knows%20me%20well%E2%80%A6%20maybe%20too%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThroughout%20this%20tiresome%20experiment%20(my%20thumbs%20are%20still%20recovering)%2C%20I%20became%20hyper-aware%20that%20TikTok%20at%20least%20vaguely%20understood%20that%20I%20would%20be%20interested%20in%20the%20same%20advertising%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20I%20received%20%3Cem%3Eso%3C%2Fem%3E%20many%20advertisements%20for%20wigs.%20Although%20I%20don't%20wear%20wigs%2C%20it%20was%20clear%20that%20the%20algorithm%20believed%20that%20I%20was%20a%20Black%20woman%20or%20knew%20that%20I%20was%20interested%20in%20content%20that%20involved%20Black%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20me%20two%20hours%20to%20finish%20watching%20500%20TikToks%3B%20just%20over%2064%25%20of%20the%20content%20I%20saw%20was%20regular%20content%2C%20meaning%20the%20remaining%2036%25%20was%20related%20to%20a%20product%20of%20some%20kind%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20it%20was%20an%20explicit%20ad%20or%20a%20review.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20often%20seek%20out%20advice%20for%20products%20on%20TikTok%2C%20so%20I%20wasn't%20surprised%20that%205%25%20of%20the%20content%20I%20saw%20was%20from%20people%20who%20reviewed%20products%2C%20often%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Ftiktok-cleaning-product-overload-trend-could-be-dangerous-experts-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BCleanTok%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20products%20%E2%80%94%20items%20popularized%20by%20content%20creators%20who%20feature%20themselves%20cleaning%20and%20sanitizing%20their%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E31%25%20of%20the%20content%20I%20saw%20was%20some%20sort%20of%20explicit%20advertisement.%20Only%20one%20ad%20I%20saw%20was%20not%20intended%20to%20sell%20a%20product%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20a%20promotion%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40trevorproject%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrevor%20Project.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22786%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20pie%20chart%20with%20Hannah's%20results%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654eea09b788914e55548223%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22490%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHannah's%20results%3Cp%3EInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20these%20videos%20were%20stacked%2C%20meaning%20I%20would%20see%20an%20affiliate%20ad%20on%20top%20of%20a%20traditional%20ad%2C%20or%20a%20traditional%20ad%20on%20top%20of%20a%20business%20promoting%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20longest%20break%20I%20had%20between%20product-related%20content%20was%20nine%20videos%2C%20although%20that%20wasn't%20common.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20percentage%20of%20ads%20appeared%20typical%20of%20a%20network%20TV%20program%2C%20which%20can%20consist%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Fstatistics%2F1025656%2Fad-time-primetime-national-tv-on-cable-networks-us%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eup%20to%2017%20minutes%20of%20ads%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20hour%20%E2%80%94%20or%20about%2028%25%20of%20programming.%20The%20key%20difference%20is%20that%20you%20scroll%20past%20a%20TikTok%20ad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESebastian's%20Experience%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20name%20is%20Sebastian%2C%20and%20I'm%20a%20queer%2022-year-old%20living%20in%20the%20Bay%20Area.%20I%20like%20watching%20horror%20movies%2C%20reading%2C%20overelaborate%20skincare%20routines%2C%20and%20spending%20too%20much%20time%20trying%20out%20advanced%20crafts%20that%20I've%20never%20attempted%2C%20with%20often%20poor%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20lay%20all%20these%20things%20about%20myself%20out%20so%20that%20you%2C%20too%2C%20can%20be%20horrified%20about%20how%20well%20my%20TikTok%20page%20seems%20to%20know%20me%20despite%20my%20pride%20in%20maintaining%20a%20mysterious%20online%20front.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20a%20Gen%20Z%2C%20my%20content-consuming%20capabilities%20were%20truly%20tested%20by%20watching%20500%20TikToks%20in%20a%20row.%20It%20was%20the%20modern-day%20equivalent%20of%20when%20my%20ancestors%20had%20to%20spend%20all%20day%20outside%20hunting%20for%20food%20or%20whatever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPredictably%2C%20my%20content%20was%20a%20well-tailored%20mix%20of%20niche%20movie%20suggestions%2C%20queer%20theory%20discourse%2C%20and%20lots%20and%20lots%20of%20crocheting%20advice.%20Nothing%20out%20of%20the%20ordinary%20for%20a%20jaunt%20onto%20my%20For%20You%20Page.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20I%20started%20noticing%20the%20ads%2C%20though%2C%20I%20couldn't%20stop.%20Before%20starting%20my%20%26quot%3Bresearch%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20was%20annoyed%20with%20how%20many%20ads%20I%20saw%2C%20but%20I%20wouldn't%20say%20I%20considered%20them%20truly%20obstructive%20to%20my%20content-viewing%20experience.%20Once%20I%20started%20paying%20attention%2C%20though%2C%20I%20realized%20I%20saw%20an%20ad%20after%20every%20two%20or%20three%20regular%20TikToks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22792%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Pie%20chart%20showing%20Sebastian's%20results%20%E2%80%94%20the%20smallest%20sliver%20is%20for%20%26quot%3Bproduct%20reviews.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654ed7c1b788914e55548000%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPie%20chart%20showing%20Sebastian's%20results%20%E2%80%94%20the%20smallest%20sliver%20is%20for%20%26quot%3Bproduct%20reviews.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20ads%20seemed%20random%2C%20but%20lots%20weren't%20%E2%80%94%20I%20saw%20a%20lot%20of%20advertisements%20for%20skincare%20and%20self-care%20products%2C%20and%20some%20sites%20advertising%20used%20books%20and%20literary%20merchandise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20did%20see%20ads%20for%20things%20I'm%20uninterested%20in%2C%20too%2C%20like%20an%20incredible%20number%20of%20ads%20for%20Macy's%2C%20which%20is%20apparently%20still%20kicking.%20I%20also%20saw%20at%20least%2010%20ads%20for%20the%20new%20Disney%20movie%20%26quot%3BWish%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20has%20a%20script%20that%20seems%20like%20it%20was%20produced%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20a%20writer's%20strike.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20several%20Sisyphean%20hours%2C%20during%20which%20I%20questioned%20my%20commitment%20to%20my%20craft%2C%20I%20saw%20360%20regular%20TikToks%20and%20140%20ads%2C%20most%20of%20which%20were%20traditional-style%20or%20influencer-sponsored%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20breaks%20down%20to%2071.8%25%20regular%20TikToks%20and%2029.2%25%20advertisements%20in%20the%20content%20I%20consumed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'It's%20helping%20people%20find%20things%20that%20they%20need'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20thing%20we%20took%20out%20of%20our%20experiment%20is%20the%20astounding%20amount%20of%20products%20advertised%20to%20us%20daily%2C%20often%20without%20us%20fully%20comprehending%20their%20influence.%20Even%20the%20most%20conscientious%20of%20us%20have%20probably%20bought%20something%20they%20would%20have%20had%20no%20idea%20about%20if%20they%20weren't%20on%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKristen%20Schiele%2C%20a%20USC%20Marshall%20School%20of%20Business%20professor%2C%20told%20Insider%20we%20could%20see%20an%20increased%20ad%20volume%20since%20advertisers%20push%20more%20ad%20content%20around%20the%20holiday%20season.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Schiele%2C%20some%20200%20million%20hours%20of%20video%20are%20streamed%20daily%20using%20TikTok%2C%20making%20its%20impact%20enormous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20spending%20more%20time%20on%20TikTok.%20You're%20going%20to%20see%20more%20ads%20because%20people%20are%20spending%20more%20time%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Schiele%20said.%20%26quot%3BAdvertisers%20are%20willing%20to%20pay%20more%20because%20that's%20where%20their%20audience%20is.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20whether%20or%20not%20there%20are%20more%20product%20promotions%20on%20TikTok%20than%20there%20used%20to%20be%20(although%20it%20sure%20feels%20like%20it)%2C%20but%20one%20thing%20is%20clear%20%E2%80%94%20there%20is%20no%20escaping%20advertising%20in%20this%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStreaming%20services%20are%20introducing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstreaming-services-ad-tiers-hulu-disney-netflix-increase-ads-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20ads%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20their%20movies%20and%20shows%20this%20year.%20Previous%20reports%20say%20cable%20networks%20insert%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Fbusiness%2Fstory%2F2019-08-02%2Ftv-networks-vowed-to-cut-back-on-commercials-instead-they-stuffed-in-more%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAfter%2520declining%2520in%25202017%252C%2520the%2Cof%25202019%252C%2520an%2520analyst%2520says.%26amp%3Btext%3DDoes%2520it%2520seem%2520like%2520there%2CYou%2527re%2520not%2520imagining%2520it.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvertising%20%3C%2Fa%3Einto%20their%20programming.%20And%20on%20other%20social%20media%20sites%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2FInstagram%2Fcomments%2Fuevhp0%2Fokay_we_get_it_your_feed_is_entirely_ads%2F%3Futm_source%3Dshare%26utm_medium%3Dweb2x%26context%3D3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInstagram%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20users%20have%20also%20complained%20about%20increased%20advertisements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDepending%20on%20how%20long%20we%20spend%20plugged%20into%20our%20devices%2C%20we%20could%20absorb%20more%20%26quot%3Binfluence%26quot%3B%20than%20we%20think.%20According%20to%20data%20cited%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2Fbusiness%2Fen-GB%2Fblog%2Ftiktok-works-driving-business-impact%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETikTok%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20about%2037%25%20of%20users%20have%20purchased%20something%20they%20discovered%20on%20the%20platform.%20And%2C%20with%20the%20platform's%20lofty%20aspirations%20to%20beat%20out%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-to-take-on-amazon-4x-shopping-business-report-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20an%20e-commerce%20behemoth%2C%20users%20might%20not%20even%20have%20to%20leave%20the%20app%20to%20make%20those%20purchases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIs%20this%20a%20good%20thing%20or%20a%20bad%20thing%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20the%20crushing%20doom%20of%20AI%20taking%20over%20our%20society%2C%20we%20suppose%20it%20depends%20on%20your%20point%20of%20view.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETikTok%20and%20other%20social%20media%20platforms%20can%2C%20in%20some%20instances%2C%20democratize%20viral%20moments%20and%20allow%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-to-take-on-amazon-4x-shopping-business-report-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esmall%20businesses%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20thrive.%20So%20far%2C%20over%20200%2C000%20businesses%20use%20TikTok%20Shop%20to%20sell%20their%20products%2C%20per%20a%20TikTok%20spokesperson.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20platform%20has%20resulted%20in%20a%20fair%20share%20of%20success%20stories%2C%20a%20TikTok%20spokesperson%20told%20Insider.%20One%20example%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40sooslick%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESoo%20Slick%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20shapewear%20brand%20founded%20by%20Nigerian%20immigrant%20Elizabeth%20Adeoye.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdeoye%20told%20Insider%20that%20she's%20been%20able%20to%20generate%20%241%20million%20in%20monthly%20sales%20through%20the%20platform%20and%20affiliate%20program%20since%20she%20began%20posting%20her%20products%20earlier%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdeoye%20said%20before%20joining%20the%20platform%2C%20she%20spent%20thousands%20on%20buying%20ads%2C%20conducting%20market%20research%2C%20and%20paying%20influencers%20to%20promote%20products.%20All%20of%20those%20costs%20disappeared%20once%20she%20joined%20TikTok%20shop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20said%20that%20the%20platform%20has%20helped%20her%20better%20serve%20her%20customers.%20For%20example%2C%20her%20followers%20help%20her%20decide%20what%20designs%20to%20sell%20next.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTikTok%20has%20all%20around%20supporting%20Black%20small%20businesses%2C%26quot%3B%20Adeoye%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey've%20been%20really%2C%20really%2C%20really%20supportive%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20my%20exposure%2C%20brand%20exposure%2C%20and%20giving%20us%20credit%20for%20advertisements%20and%20stuff%20like%20that.%20They've%20just%20definitely%20been%20a%20huge%20part%20of%20my%20success%20so%20far.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20it%20seems%20like%20more%20and%20more%2C%20the%20platform%20is%20becoming%20a%20place%20where%20people%20want