was%20a%20stalwart%20of%20the%20freedom%20struggle%20who%20stood%20out%20amongst%20a%20galaxy%20of%20leaders%20on%20account%20of%20his%20intellectual%20prowess%20and%20deep%20commitment%20to%20the%20nationalist%20politics%20of%2020th-century%20India.%20He%20was%20a%20profound%20thinker%2C%20an%20interpreter%20of%20religion%2C%20an%20upholder%20of%20secularism%2C%20and%20one%20of%20the%20builders%20of%20the%20modern%20Indian%20state.%20He%20was%20a%20rare%20combination%20of%20high%20learning%2C%20deep%20intellect%2C%20and%20revolutionary%20activity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAzad%E2%80%99s%20father%2C%20Muhammed%20Khairuddin%2C%20was%20a%20scholar%20and%20mystic.%20He%20wrote%20numerous%20books%20in%20Arabic%20and%20Persian%2C%20and%20had%20a%20large%20number%20of%20disciples%20in%20Delhi%2C%20Gujarat%2C%20Maharashtra%2C%20and%20Calcutta.%20Being%20the%20son%20of%20a%20religious%20leader%2C%20Azad%20received%20his%20early%20education%20in%20the%20traditional%20manner%2C%20directly%20under%20the%20supervision%20of%20his%20father.%20After%20acquiring%20proficiency%20in%20Arabic%20and%20Persian%2C%20he%20studied%20Philosophy%2C%20Mathematics%2C%20and%20Algebra.%20He%20completed%20the%20entire%20course%20of%20study%20by%20the%20time%20he%20was%2016.%20Soon%20after%2C%20he%20became%20a%20teacher%20of%20Philosophy%2C%20Mathematics%20and%20Logic%2C%20and%20quickly%20earned%20recognition%20as%20a%20scholar%20in%20Arabic%20and%20Persian%20and%20in%20Islamic%20theology.%20Azad%20had%20inherited%20from%20his%20father%20the%20temperament%20of%20a%20scholar%2C%20but%20his%20thirst%20for%20knowledge%20and%20his%20passion%20for%20action%20did%20not%20permit%20him%20to%20lead%20the%20quiet%20life%20of%20a%20teacher%20and%20religious%20leader.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20age%20of%2020%2C%20he%20toured%20the%20West%20Asian%20countries%20and%20came%20in%20contact%20with%20Arab%20and%20Turkish%20revolutionaries%20who%20were%20working%20for%20the%20freedom%20of%20their%20lands.%20Abul%20Kalam%20was%20inspired%20by%20these%20people%2C%20and%20on%20his%20return%20to%20India%2C%20he%20entered%20politics%20and%20started%20%3Cem%3EAl%20Hilal%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20an%20Urdu%20weekly%2C%20from%20Calcutta%20in%201912%20to%20propagate%20his%20ideas.%20The%20first%20issue%20of%20%3Cem%3EAl%20Hilal%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20published%20on%20June%201%2C%201912.%20Abul%20Kalam%20was%20only%2024%20then%2C%20but%20he%20had%20already%20been%20accepted%20as%20%E2%80%98Maulana%E2%80%99%20by%20Muslim%20theologists.%20From%20the%20very%20day%20of%20its%20inception%2C%20%3Cem%3EAl%20Hilal%3C%2Fem%3E%20took%20its%20stand%20against%20British%20rule%20in%20India.%20In%20the%20pages%20of%20this%20journal%2C%20he%20wrote%20editorials%20which%20were%20remarkable%20for%20their%20beauty%20of%20style%20and%20forcefulness%20of%20language.%20Through%20these%2C%20the%20Maulana%20urged%20the%20Muslims%20of%20India%20to%20come%20out%20of%20their%20self-imposed%20political%20indifference%20and%20cooperate%20with%20their%20Hindu%20brethren%20in%20the%20task%20of%20freeing%20the%20country%20from%20foreign%20rule.%20This%20was%20a%20bold%20and%20new%20line%20of%20thinking%20for%20Indian%20Muslims%20and%20it%20created%20a%20great%20stir%20among%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fmaulana-abul-kamal-azad-sedition%5C%22%3EOn%20His%20Birth%20Anniversary%2C%20Remembering%20What%20Maulana%20Abul%20Kalam%20Azad%20Said%20About%20Sedition%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEver%20since%20the%20unsuccessful%20Indian%20revolt%20of%201857%2C%20Indian%20Muslims%20had%20been%20living%20in%20an%20atmosphere%20of%20despair%20and%20lack%20of%20faith.%20Some%20Muslim%20leaders%20like%20Sir%20Syed%20Ahmed%20Khan%20tried%20to%20restore%20the%20confidence%20of%20the%20Indian%20Muslims%20by%20pursuing%20a%20policy%20of%20gaining%20the%20favour%20of%20the%20ruling%20power%20and%20keeping%20away%20from%20the%20field%20of%20active%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F02%2F17153651%2FThe-recapture-of-Delhi.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-225064%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22538%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERevolt%20of%201857.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20Maulana%20Azad%2C%20this%20policy%20appeared%20not%20only%20unpatriotic%20but%20also%20un-Islamic.%20He%20realised%20that%20the%20interests%20of%20Indian%20Muslims%20could%20be%20served%20only%20if%20they%20took%20part%20in%20the%20national%20struggle%20for%20independence.%20He%20felt%20that%20the%20liberation%20of%20India%20was%20necessary%20for%20the%20progress%20and%20prosperity%20of%20the%20entire%20Muslim%20world.%20From%201920%20till%201945%20Abul%20Kalam%20Azad%20was%20in%20and%20out%20of%20prison%20a%20number%20of%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20he%20was%20released%20from%20Ranchi%2C%20he%20was%20elected%20president%20of%20the%20All-India%20Khilafat%20Committee%20(Calcutta%20session%20in%201920)%2C%20and%20president%20of%20the%20Unity%20Conference%20(Delhi)%20in%201924.%20In%201928%2C%20he%20presided%20over%20the%20Nationalist%20Muslim%20Conference.%20He%20was%20appointed%20in%201937%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Congress%20parliamentary%20sub-committee%20to%20guide%20the%20Provincial%20Congress%20ministries.%20He%20was%20twice%20elected%20president%20of%20the%20Indian%20National%20Congress%2C%20the%20first%20time%20in%201923%20when%20he%20was%20only%2035%20years%20old%2C%20and%20the%20second%20time%20in%201940.%20Addressing%20the%20delegates%20at%20the%20Congress%20session%20in%20Ramgarh%20(Jharkhand)%20the%20Maulana%20stated%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EI%20am%20a%20Muslim%20and%20profoundly%20conscious%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20I%20have%20inherited%20glorious%20traditions%20of%20the%20last%20thirteen%20hundred%20years.%20I%20am%20not%20prepared%20to%20lose%20even%20a%20small%20part%20of%20that%20legacy.%20The%20history%20and%20teachings%20of%20Islam%2C%20its%20arts%20and%20letters%2C%20its%20civilisation%20and%20culture%2C%20are%20part%20of%20my%20wealth%20and%20it%20is%20my%20duty%20to%20cherish%20and%20guard%20them.%20As%20a%20Muslim%2C%20I%20have%20a%20special%20identity%20within%20the%20field%20of%20religion%20and%20culture%E2%80%A6%20But%2C%20with%20all%20these%20feelings%2C%20I%20have%20another%20equally%20deep%20realisation%2C%20born%20out%20of%20my%20life%E2%80%99s%20experience%2C%20which%20is%20strengthened%20and%20not%20hindered%20by%20the%20spirit%20of%20Islam.%20I%20am%20equally%20proud%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20I%20am%20an%20Indian%2C%20an%20essential%20part%20of%20the%20indivisible%20unity%20of%20Indian%20nationhood%2C%20a%20vital%20factor%20in%20its%20total%20makeup%20without%20which%20this%20noble%20edifice%20will%20remain%20incomplete.%20I%20can%20never%20give%20up%20this%20sincere%20claim.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20historian%20S.%20Irfan%20Habib%2C%20this%20was%20Azad%E2%80%99s%20response%20to%20the%20exclusivist%20and%20faith-based%20nationalism%20of%20Savarkar%2C%20which%20aided%20the%20Muslim%20communalists%20led%20by%20the%20League%20to%20instil%20fear%20among%20Muslims%20about%20their%20future%20in%20united%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMaulana%20Azad%20concluded%20his%20presidential%20address%20thus%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EOur%20shared%20life%20of%20a%20thousand%20years%20has%20forged%20a%20common%20nationality.%20Such%20moulds%20cannot%20be%20artificially%20constructed.%20Nature%E2%80%99s%20hidden%20anvils%20shape%20them%20over%20the%20centuries.%20The%20mould%20has%20now%20been%20cast%20and%20destiny%20has%20set%20her%20seal%20upon%20it.%20Whether%20we%20like%20it%20or%20not%2C%20we%20have%20now%20become%20an%20Indian%20nation%2C%20united%20and%20indivisible.%20No%20false%20idea%20of%20separatism%20can%20break%20our%20oneness.%20We%20must%20accept%20the%20inexorable%20logic%20of%20facts%20and%20apply%20ourselves%20to%20fashioning%20our%20future%20density.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20continued%20as%20the%20president%20of%20the%20Congress%20till%201946%2C%20for%20no%20election%20was%20held%20during%20this%20period%20as%20almost%20every%20Congress%20leader%20was%20in%20prison%20on%20account%20of%20the%20Quit%20India%20Movement%20(1942).%20After%20the%20leaders%20were%20released%20Maulana%20Azad%2C%20as%20the%20president%20of%20the%20Congress%2C%20led%20the%20negotiations%20with%20the%20British%20Cabinet%20Mission%20in%201946%2C%20and%20when%20India%20became%20independent%20he%20was%20appointed%20education%20minister%2C%20a%20position%20in%20which%20he%20continued%20till%20his%20death%20on%20February%2022%2C%201958.%20His%20role%20as%20India%E2%80%99s%20first%20minister%20for%20education%20was%20marvellous.%20Besides%20setting%20up%20many%20scientific%20and%20technological%20institutions%2C%20he%20founded%20the%20Indian%20Council%20of%20Cultural%20Relations%20as%20also%20the%20three%20%E2%80%98akademis%E2%80%99%20devoted%20to%20arts%2C%20literature%20and%20music.%20He%20thus%20substantially%20contributed%20to%20the%20fulfilment%20of%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20vision%20of%20modern%20and%20liberal%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Freview-irfan-habibs-maulana-azad-a-life-is-a-voice-of-reason-and-unity-in-times-of-hate%5C%22%3EReview%3A%20Irfan%20Habib%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Maulana%20Azad%3A%20A%20Life%E2%80%99%20Is%20a%20Voice%20of%20Reason%20and%20Unity%20in%20Times%20of%20Hate%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20events%20in%20Maulana%E2%80%99s%20life%20in%20the%20years%20leading%20to%20independence%20are%20worth%20recalling.%20In%201939%2C%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%2C%20opposed%20to%20the%20re-election%20of%20Subhas%20Chandra%20Bose%20as%20president%20of%20the%20Indian%20National%20Congress%2C%20proposed%20Azad%E2%80%99s%20name%2C%20but%20the%20latter%2C%20after%20initially%20accepting%20the%20offer%2C%20withdrew%20from%20the%20contest.%20This%20was%20politically%20correct%20as%20a%20contest%20against%20Subhas%20Chandra%20Bose%2C%20who%20was%20then%20at%20the%20peak%20of%20his%20popularity%2C%20was%20too%20risky.%20Hence%20Azad%20chose%20discretion%20as%20the%20better%20part%20of%20valour.%20Like%20Gandhi%2C%20Maulana%20Azad%20was%20opposed%20to%20the%20partition%20of%20India%20right%20till%20the%20end.%20But%20unlike%20the%20Frontier%20Gandhi%2C%20and%20like%20Gandhi%2C%20he%20ultimately%20gave%20in%20to%20the%20Mountbatten%20Plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20historian%20Rajmohan%20Gandhi%2C%20%E2%80%9CBy%20the%20end%20of%20March%201947%2C%20Patel%20had%20become%20keen%20on%20division%20and%2C%20later%2C%20Nehru%20too%20was%20reconciled%20to%20it%20%E2%80%94%20Azad%20too%20acquiesced.%20In%20%3Cem%3EIndia%20Wins%20Freedom%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20he%20has%20written%20of%20his%20battles%20to%20prevent%20division%20but%20at%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20meetings%2C%20he%20did%20not%20oppose%20the%20Mountbatten%20Plan.%20Neither%20the%20Mahatma%20nor%20the%20Maulana%20defied%20Nehru%20and%20Patel%20who%20were%20backed%20by%20Rajagopalachari%2C%20Rajendra%20Prasad%2C%20Govind%20Ballabh%20Pant%20and%20many%20others.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20corroborated%20by%20Acharya%20Kripalani%2C%20Congress%20President%20in%201946%2C%20and%20a%20bitter%20critic%20of%20Azad.%20The%20Acharya%20writes%20in%20his%20biography%20of%20Mahatma%3A%20%E2%80%9CIn%20his%20book%20%3Cem%3EIndia%20Wins%20Freedom%3C%2Fem%3E%20(pp.%20192-97)%2C%20Maulana%20Azad%20has%20said%20that%20he%20was%20against%20partition%20and%20that%20he%20had%20made%20his%20opinion%20clear%20to%20Gandhiji.%20I%20do%20not%20know%20what%20private%20conferences%20he%20had%20with%20Gandhiji.%20All%20I%20know%20is%20that%20he%20never%20opposed%20it%20in%20the%20Working%20Committee%20or%20the%20AICC.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%20partition%2C%20deeply%20hurt%20and%20angry%2C%20addressing%20a%20vast%20multitude%20from%20the%20pulpit%20of%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20Jama%20Masjid%20the%20Maulana%20gave%20them%20hope%20and%20confidence%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EI%20told%20you%20that%20the%20two-nation%20theory%20was%20the%20death%20knell%20of%20a%20life%20of%20faith%20and%20belief%20%E2%80%A6%20Those%20on%20whom%20you%20relied%20for%20support%20have%20forsaken%20you%2C%20left%20you%20helpless%20%E2%80%A6.%20dear%20brethren%20!%20I%20have%20no%20new%20antidote%20for%20you%2C%20only%20something%20that%20was%20brought%20about%201400%20years%20ago%E2%80%A6.%20do%20not%20fear%20and%20do%20not%20grieve.%20And%20you%20will%20indeed%20gain%20the%20upper%20hand%20if%20you%20are%20possessed%20of%20true%20faith.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMaulana%20Azad%20died%20on%20February%2022%2C%201958%2C%20before%20he%20turned%2070.%20A%20week%20before%20he%20died%20prime%20minister%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20visited%20the%20ailing%20Maulana%20who%20looked%20in%20the%20eyes%20of%20his%20beloved%20friend%20and%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CJawahar%20%3Cem%3EKhuda%20Hafiz.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fem%3ENo%20better%20words%20could%20express%20the%20personality%20of%20the%20great%20scholar%20than%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20tribute%20in%20Parliament%20on%20February%2024%2C%201958%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20has%20become%20almost%20a%20commonplace%2C%20when%20a%20prominent%20person%20passes%20away%2C%20to%20say%20that%20he%20is%20irreplaceable.%20That%20is%20often%20true%3B%20yet%2C%20I%20believe%20that%20it%20is%20literally%20and%20absolutely%20true%20in%20regard%20to%20the%20passing%20away%20of%20Maulana%20Azad.%20We%20have%20had%20great%20men%20and%20we%20will%20have%20great%20men%2C%20but%20I%20do%20submit%20that%20the%20peculiar%20and%20special%20type%20of%20greatness%20which%20Maulana%20Azad%20represented%20is%20not%20likely%20to%20be%20reproduced%20in%20India%20or%20anywhere%20else%20%E2%80%94%20we%20mourn%20today%20the%20passing%20of%20a%20great%20man%2C%20a%20man%20of%20luminous%20intelligence%20and%20mighty%20intellect%20with%20an%20amazing%20capacity%20to%20pierce%20through%20a%20problem%20to%20its%20core.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndeed%20the%20greatness%20of%20Maulana%2C%20like%20Nehru%20himself%2C%20cannot%20be%20reproduced%20here%20or%20anywhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPraveen%20Davar%20is%20an%20ex-Army%20officer%2C%20a%20columnist%2C%20and%20the%20author%20of%3C%2Fem%3E%20Freedom%20Struggle%20and%20Beyond.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699685425000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F03%2F28210929%2Fog-maulana-abul-kalam-azad-5282.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fremembering-maulana-abul-kalam-azad-a-scholar-patriot-and-builder-of-modern-india%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Today%2C%20November%2011%2C%20marks%20the%20135th%20birth%20anniversary%20of%20India's%20first%20education%20minister.%20The%20Maulana%20played%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20bringing%20Indian%20Muslims%20out%20of%20their%20self-imposed%20political%20indifference%20to%20cooperate%20with%20their%20Hindu%20brethren%20in%20the%20task%20of%20freeing%20the%20country%20from%20foreign%20rule.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A53%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fremembering-maulana-abul-kalam-azad-a-scholar-patriot-and-builder-of-modern-india%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Rise%20and%20Shine%20Acquires%20%E2%80%98Selling%20a%20Colonial%20War%E2%80%99%20Ahead%20of%20World%20Premiere%20at%20IDFA%3A%20%E2%80%98This%20Will%20Be%20Dynamite%20in%20the%20Netherlands%E2%80%99%20(EXCLUSIVE)%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699684971000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2FSelling-a-Colonial-War.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https