bal%20Leaders%20Forum%20(ITLF)%20met%20with%20the%20members%20of%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20(MHA)%2C%20in%20Manipur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20meeting%E2%80%99s%20objective%20was%20to%20evaluate%20the%20previous%20session%20with%20the%20Union%20home%20minister%20on%20August%208%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20which%20had%20focused%20on%20the%20burial%20site%20issue%20between%20the%20Meitei%20and%20Kuki%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20burial%20issue%20goes%20back%20to%20August%203%2C%20when%20members%20of%20the%20Kuki%20community%20sought%20to%20bury%20their%20fellow%20members%2C%20who%20had%20been%20killed%20since%20the%20violence%20began%20on%20May%203%2C%20in%20an%20open%20field%20in%20S.%20Boljang%20village%2C%20which%2C%20as%20per%20their%20claim%2C%20falls%20within%20the%20Churachandpur%20district.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Meiteis%20said%20that%20the%20area%20belonged%20to%20the%20Meitei-dominating%20Bishnupur%20district.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20announcement%20of%20a%20burial%20by%20the%20Kuki-Zo%20community%20on%20August%203%20heightened%20tensions%20at%20the%20border%2C%20resulting%20in%20hundreds%20of%20men%20from%20both%20communities%20gathering%20at%20the%20Bishnupur-Churachandpur%20border.%20Subsequently%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20intervened.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20second%20meeting%20between%20ITLF%20and%20MHA.%20As%20earlier%20mentioned%2C%20the%20first%20meeting%20happened%20on%20August%208%20in%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20following%20issues%20were%20discussed%20in%20the%20meeting%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%93%20ITLF%20addressed%20the%20breach%20of%20their%20agreement%20regarding%20the%20State%20commando%20in%20Moreh.%20It%20emphasised%20the%20need%20for%20the%20complete%20removal%20of%20state%20forces%20from%20hill%20areas.%20Although%20the%20ministry%20asserted%20the%20inability%20to%20entirely%20withdraw%20state%20forces%2C%20a%20commitment%20was%20made%20to%20prevent%20independent%20state%20force%20actions%20in%20hill%20areas.%20Acknowledging%20a%20lapse%20in%20Moreh%2C%20the%20government%20assured%20that%20such%20incidents%20would%20be%20avoided%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%93%20In%20terms%20of%20political%20demands%2C%20interlocutor%20A.K.%20Mishra%20highlighted%20the%20Suspension%20of%20Operations%20(SoO)%20group%E2%80%99s%20pending%20demands%20awaiting%20government%20approval.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Manipur%2C%20there%20are%20around%2030%20Kuki%20insurgent%20groups%2C%20with%2025%20engaged%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-politics%2Fwhat-is-the-soo-agreement-manipur-govt-withdrew-from-8494829%2F%5C%22%3Etripartite%20SoO%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20and%20the%20state.%20Among%20them%2C%2017%20fall%20under%20the%20Kuki%20National%20Organisation%20(KNO)%2C%20and%20eight%20are%20part%20of%20the%20United%20People%E2%80%99s%20Front%20(UPF).%20The%20SoO%20pact%2C%20initiated%20on%20August%2022%2C%202008%2C%20aims%20to%20facilitate%20political%20dialogue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOriginally%20advocating%20for%20a%20separate%20Kuki%20state%2C%20the%20groups%20have%20now%20scaled%20down%20their%20demands%20to%20a%20%E2%80%98Kukiland%20territorial%20council%E2%80%99%20with%20financial%20and%20administrative%20autonomy%20from%20the%20Manipur%20Assembly%20and%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%93%20Mishra%20also%20urged%20ITLF%20to%20refrain%20from%20resorting%20to%20violent%20means.%20While%20ITLF%20leaders%20expressed%20their%20desire%20for%20peace%2C%20they%20emphasised%20the%20need%20to%20defend%20themselves%20when%20provoked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%93%20ITLF%20also%20raised%20concerns%20about%20selective%20justice%20by%20the%20National%20Investigative%20Agency%20and%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20(CBI)%2C%20saying%20that%20some%20gruesome%20cases%20were%20not%20taken%20up%20by%20CBI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20government%20assured%20that%20justice%20would%20be%20pursued%20in%20these%20cases%20with%20the%20CBI%20and%20NIA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%93%20ITLF%20expressed%20gratitude%20for%20the%20release%20and%20transfer%20of%20minor%20cases%20among%20jail%20inmates.%20It%20urged%20the%20government%20to%20expedite%20the%20process%20for%20the%20remaining%20inmates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%93%20It%20voiced%20concerns%20about%20the%20thousands%20of%20looted%20arms%20in%20civilian%20hands.%20To%20this%2C%20MHA%20leaders%20assured%20efforts%20to%20collect%20these%20arms%20and%20emphasised%20on%20the%20need%20for%20a%20similar%20initiative%20in%20Churachandpur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20meeting%20reached%20a%20deadlock%2C%20but%20there%20are%20plans%20to%20reconvene%20the%20meeting%20tomorrow%20(November%2010).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20far%20in%20Manipur%2C%20violence%20has%20persisted%20for%20over%20six%20months%2C%20and%20more%20than%20200%20people%20have%20lost%20their%20lives%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699550789000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09225411%2Fimage-1493.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmanipur-itlf-mha-second-meeting-addresses-burial-site-conflict-between-kuki-and-meitei-communities%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20meeting%20reached%20a%20deadlock%2C%20but%20there%20are%20plans%20to%20reconvene%20the%20meeting%20on%20November%2010.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmanipur-itlf-mha-second-meeting-addresses-burial-site-conflict-between-kuki-and-meitei-communities%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20Rejects%20Australian%20Court%E2%80%99s%20Jurisdiction%20in%20Judgment%20Against%20Former%20Indian%20Diplomat%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09221829%2F272741300_300937185402961_3315864555464272419_n.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20India%20rejected%20the%20jurisdiction%20of%20an%20Australian%20court%20over%20its%20ex-parte%20direction%20to%20its%20former%20high%20commissioner%20to%20pay%20a%20penalty%20to%20an%20Indian%20staff%20member%20for%20violating%20local%20wage%20standards%20and%20announced%20plans%20on%20Thursday%2C%20November%209%2C%20to%20address%20the%20issue%20with%20Australian%20authorities.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20November%203%2C%20an%20Australian%20federal%20court%20ordered%20India%E2%80%99s%20former%20high%20commissioner%20to%20Canberra%20Navdeep%20Singh%20Suri%20to%20pay%20A%24136%2C000%20to%20a%20former%20staff%20member%20employed%20at%20the%20official%20residence%20for%20not%20paying%20her%20as%20per%20Australia%E2%80%99s%202009%20Fair%20Work%20Act.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Faustralia-domestic-help-high-commissioner%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20had%20reported%20earlier%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20the%20implications%20of%20the%20judgment%20on%20diplomatic%20privileges%20and%20immunities%2C%20since%20the%20complainant%20Seema%20Shergill%20had%20been%20in%20Australia%20with%20an%20official%20passport%20with%20a%20diplomatic%20visa%20during%20the%20period%20of%20the%20dispute.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20first%20response%20from%20India%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20(MEA)%20spokesperson%20Arindam%20Bagchi%20said%20that%20New%20Delhi%20%E2%80%9Creject%5Bs%5D%20any%20locus%20standi%20of%20Australian%20authorities%20to%20adjudicate%20on%20matters%20concerning%20such%20India-based%20Service%20Staff%20of%20the%20High%20Commission%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStating%20that%20India%20was%20%E2%80%9Ctaking%20up%20the%20matter%E2%80%9D%20with%20Australia%2C%20Bagchi%20urged%20Canberra%20%E2%80%9Cto%20uphold%20its%20obligations%20under%20the%20Vienna%20Convention%20on%20Diplomatic%20Relations%2C%20particularly%20in%20relation%20to%20diplomatic%20immunities%20and%20privileges%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESeema%20Shergill%20had%20travelled%20with%20Suri%20as%20India-based%20service%20staff%20in%202015.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20she%20left%20the%20official%20residence%2C%20known%20as%20India%20House%2C%20without%20information.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBagchi%20claimed%20that%20Shergill%20had%20%E2%80%9Cwillfully%20deserted%20her%20post%20in%20May%202016%2C%20a%20day%20before%20her%20scheduled%20return%20to%20India%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CSince%20then%2C%20we%20have%20repeatedly%20requested%20Australian%20authorities%20to%20locate%20and%20repatriate%20her%20to%20India.%20We%20have%20learnt%20that%20she%20has%20made%20allegations%20against%20the%20then%20High%20Commissioner%2C%20and%20an%20ex-%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eparte%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20judgment%20has%20now%20been%20issued%20by%20an%20Australian%20court%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20noted.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPointing%20out%20that%20she%20was%20an%20India-based%20service%20staff%20at%20the%20diplomatic%20mission%2C%20the%20MEA%20spokesperson%20asserted%20that%20any%20grievance%20had%20to%20be%20redressed%20only%20in%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CHer%20conduct%20and%20false%20representations%20give%20rise%20to%20suspicions%20that%20all%20this%20has%20been%20motivated%20by%20her%20desire%20to%20permanently%20stay%20in%20Australia%2C%20and%20in%20which%20she%20seems%20to%20have%20succeeded.%20We%20are%20also%20concerned%20by%20the%20ex-%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eparte%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20court%20judgment%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20sources%2C%20Shergill%20declined%20to%20sign%20a%20compulsory%20undertaking%20in%20May%202016%20committing%20to%20return%20to%20India%20after%20completing%20a%20three-year%20tenure%20%E2%80%93%20a%20provision%20introduced%20in%20response%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Faustralia-domestic-help-high-commissioner%5C%22%3EKhobragade%20affair%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESources%20had%20pointed%20out%20that%20diplomats%20and%20staff%20receive%20salaries%20according%20to%20Indian%20scales.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdditionally%2C%20there%20were%20concerns%20that%20the%20ruling%20might%20prompt%20service%20staff%20in%20Indian%20missions%20abroad%20to%20pursue%20compensation%20under%20local%20laws%20and%20potentially%20persuade%20them%20to%20use%20this%20as%20a%20path%20towards%20citizenship.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699548931000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09221829%2F272741300_300937185402961_3315864555464272419_n.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-rejects-australian-courts-jurisdiction-in-judgment-against-former-indian-diplomat%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20a%20former%20high%20commissioner%20was%20asked%20to%20pay%20a%20penalty%20to%20an%20Indian%20staff%20member%20for%20violating%20local%20wage%20standards%2C%20New%20Delhi%20announced%20plans%20to%20address%20the%20issue%20with%20Australian%20authorities.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-rejects-australian-courts-jurisdiction-in-judgment-against-former-indian-diplomat%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22This%20Is%20How%20Americans%20Really%20Feel%20About%20Tipping%20%E2%80%94%20And%20Who%20They're%20Likely%20To%20Tip%20Most%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22A%20new%20survey%20shows%20U.S.%20adults%20are%20fa